detailedDescription.articleBody: The Baseball Encyclopedia is a baseball reference book first published by Macmillan in 1969. Nine further editions of the book were released between 1974 and 1996. The Baseball Encyclopedia features statistical summaries for Major League Baseball players.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Kamaal Ibn John Fareed, better known by his stage name Q-Tip, is an American rapper, record producer, singer, actor and DJ. Nicknamed The Abstract, he is noted for his innovative jazz-influenced style of hip hop production and his philosophical, esoteric and introspective lyrical themes.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: कमाल इब्न जॉन फरीद, जिसे उनके मंच नाम क्यू-टिप से बेहतर जाना जाता है, एक अमेरिकी रैपर, रिकॉर्ड निर्माता, गायक, अभिनेता और डीजे, उपनाम द एब्सट्रैक्ट है, वह हिप हॉप उत्पादन की अपनी अभिनव जैज़-प्रभावित शैली और उनके दार्शनिक के लिए विख्यात है।

detailedDescription.articleBody:
Paul Jackson Pollock was an American painter and a major figure in the abstract expressionist movement.
He was widely noticed for his technique of pouring or splashing liquid household paint onto a horizontal surface, enabling him to view and paint his canvases from all angles.

detailedDescription.articleBody: The Tragedy of Hamlet, Prince of Denmark, often shortened to Hamlet, is a tragedy written by William Shakespeare sometime between 1599 and 1601. It is Shakespeare's longest play with 30,557 words.
